disappointment ... i enjoy reading food narratives and childhood accounts of growing up in foreign countries ; however , this book is quite a disappointment after reading the summary above . the writing is n't great , the descriptions certainly do n't transport you to tuscany , and despite the title , i would n't say there is an emphasis on food . if you were related to patrizia , you mind find it an interesting read , but i 've found myself skimming through it , searching for compelling passages , of which there are few